comments: Great professor. A lot of writing , but all great topics. She will challenge you. Only bad thing is, she is a very liberal thinker and tries to push it off on you. For example, she will have you read liberal papers for homework. Other than that, she is great.

tag_professor: Gives good feedback (1)  Tough Grader (1)  Skip class? You won\'t pass. (1)
comments: She\'s super sweet. A fire cracker though. She will keep you on your toes ,but you will become a way better writer after you take her class.

tag_professor: Gives good feedback (1)  Tough Grader (1)  Skip class? You won\'t pass. (1)
comments: Mrs. Bartlett is an amazing teacher. Her way of speaking is one of a kind, not to mention she has a great taste in literature as well as in fashion. She is adorable, and will make the class fun. If you are up for a challenge and are ready to work hard, this is the perfect professor.

comments: Love! Super Funny. She gives us a lot to do but its very simple! and the essays can be hard at times but very fun class.

tag_professor: Gives good feedback (1)  Tough Grader (1)  Skip class? You won\'t pass. (1)
comments: I LOVE Mrs.Bartlett! She\'s adorable and makes learning fun. This class is not for the lazy. There\'s quite a bit of writing involved, which is great for me because I love it, and some reading. I am already a better writer because of her. She\'s by far the best teacher I\'ve ever had! She\'s tiny, but fierce! I will always carry her teachings with me.

tag_professor: Gives good feedback (1)  Tough Grader (1)  Skip class? You won\'t pass. (1)
comments: Extremely picky, do not take if you want an easy Freshman Comp and your degree has nothing to do with English or Anthropology. She\'s tough and wants everyone to have extreme ideas and opinions to make her life interesting. She\'ll give you a bad grade without telling you what to do or what not to do.

Gives good feedback (1)  Tough Grader (1)  Skip class? You won\'t pass. (1)
comments: Professor Bartlett makes it clear the first day you will write. Her assignments are not hard or long, but unless your up for a challenge, take the 16 week course. We had homework just about every class. Alot of reading but the stories are short and interesting. I enjoyed her class and would take her again. Buying the text books are mandatory.
